Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">All prediction</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> indicate that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gas will continue to play a significant and increasing role in primary power generation for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">forseeable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> future, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">however </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the role of natural gas in supporting other UK industries should not be underestimated.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A large proportion of the n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">atural gas </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">demand in the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> due to a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">myriad of industrial applications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which cannot be replaced by renewables </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">including</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pulp and paper production</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">metals refining</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">stone, clay and glass, plastic, and food processing industries</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">petrochemical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">feedstocks</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In addition to industrial uses outlined above approximately 1/3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of UK gas demand is driven by domestic heating and cooking.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The recent uncertainty around the future of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ineos</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> petrochemical facility near </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Grangemouth</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'