including</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cambrian </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Tremadoc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Shales</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and Silurian shales.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Until the exploration and appraisal testing phases are completed over the coming years it is difficult to estimate what level of commercial development could be achieved.  The commerciality of any particular unconventional resource play is determined by a number of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">social</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, environmental, economic and geological criteria and at this early stag</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e every scenario from zero</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> commer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">al production through to the development of a major new industry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are still possible outcomes for the unconventional gas industry in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The potential environmental and climate change impact of extraction and use of the gas;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Various recent studies by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Royal Society, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Royal Academy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of Eng</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eering</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and Public Health England </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have all indicated a well regulated and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">well </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">executed shale </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gas </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">operation should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">significant </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impact on the environment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or public health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Nearly all the examples of environmental damage used by those opposed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">development of an indigenous </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">unconventional gas industry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">can be easily classified into the following groups: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">accidental spillages</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cases of gross negligence </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">illegal activities by individuals </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or corporations</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 88.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">due to practices </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that are incompatible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">existing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> UK regulation</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> UK has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> long history of gas processing, pipeline operation and onshore hydrocarbon drilling</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and production</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> demonstrat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">environmental risks associated with these operations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">can be effectively managed rather </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">than </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">poor environmental performance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">being a systemic and unavoidable consequence. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Climate change is a global issue and given </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that the UK contribution to global greenhouse emissions i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> &lt;1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">% of the global total it is unlikely that, in isolation, any commercial shale production in Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">indeed the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> would have a significant impact on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lobal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">climate c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hange.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However events over the last few years in the US have shown that low</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> gas prices on a continental scale can lead to a shift away from high CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">coal fired generation to lower emission gas fired generation with a net benefit in total CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> output.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Given the presence of prospective shale gas plays being identified on every inhabited continent a simple extrapolation of the US example would suggest that global development of shale gas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in conjunction with renewables and nuclear energy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> would displace coal fired power generation and lead to significant reductions in global greenhouse gas emissions over the coming decades.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Whether the current regulatory regime covering such activity is adequate;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The UK has a long history of regulating onshore hydrocarbon exploration and production through the DECC onshore licen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing regime, local or minerals planning regime, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Coal Authority, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Environment Agency or Natural Resource Wales licen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing provisions and the Health and Safety Executive. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> current</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> regulatory</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> regime is considered to provide robust protection to the environment, local communities and workforce</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Notwithstanding the previous statement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">there is a considerable amount of duplication both in the information being submitted and the number of public consultations required throughout the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">planning</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and permitting regime that introduces significant uncertainty, costs and time delays to the well planning process.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A clarification of responsibilities of each of the regulators between surface and sub-surface development and a single application for the permitting of well operations to remove the duplication currently inherent in the permitting system would be of significa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nt benefit to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">op</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">erators and would speed up the exploration and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appraisal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the shale resource.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-34.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The potential economic impact of shale gas production in Wales</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Given very early stages of shale gas exploration and appraisal in Wales with only </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">% of the total area of Wales currently licensed for oil and gas exploration it is difficult to estimate the potential impact of future shale gas development</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s previously stated the range of potential outcomes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">varies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">from almost nothing to very significant.</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-34.9pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The US example and recent reports by the Institute of Directors suggest that in the success case the unconventional hydrocarbons industry would benefit the UK, including Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> due to:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Direct and indirect job creation in a new industry</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Significant service sector and supply chain opportunities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Increased security of supply</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reduced exposure to international gas price fluctuations</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Potential reduction in wholesale gas and electricity generation</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Increased competitiveness of local industry</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81.42pt; padding-left:3.63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Increased tax revenues  </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The exact scale of th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e benefits would be directly proportional to the eventual scale of the industry in the UK, however given the UK’s leading role in unconventional development the first mover advantage could result in the export of skills, processes and supply chain to others that follow in the European or North African markets.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ignoring effects on gas price on primary energy production the benefits of an increased supply of low cost ethane</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> via domestic shale gas production</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> could have game changing effect on the petrochemicals industry.  A 2011 report by the American Chemicals Council modelled the impacts of a 25% increase in ethane availability on the petrochemicals industry in the US and concluded the following:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 73.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">17,000 new knowledge intensive jobs in the chemical industry</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 73.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">385,000 new jobs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outwith</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the chemicals industry including users of chemical end products and a result of new capital investment such as facilities construction</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 73.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">US$4.4 billion annual increase in tax take national, state and local levels</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 73.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">US$16.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> billion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in new capital investment </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 73.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">US</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">$</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">132 billion a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nnual increase in US economic out</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">put</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 81pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">While no-one is suggesting a direct replication of this in the UK or Wales </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it does go some way to demonstrating the transformational effect that domestic shale gas could have on one particular sector of the economy.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63.8pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">7.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">he role of the Wales Office and the Welsh Government in developing a policy framework for the exploration of shale gas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The onshore hydrocarbon industry welcomes strong</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, consistent and evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">based</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> regulation policed by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a strong regulator</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(s)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with defined </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">terms of reference</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  A clear demarcation between surface</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> planning</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and sub-surface regulatory regimes and removal of unnecessary burden in terms of cost and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">human </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">resources </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for both regulator(s) and operator through overlapping regulation should be a priority of any government.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Any new policy framework should aim to encourage early exploration activities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> through the removal unnecessary regulatory burdens, provision of clear and consistent guidance and encouraging investment by ensuring a stable fiscal regime during the development of this industry.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>